  "market_context": "USDCAD on the 15-minute chart with the fractal model indicator overlaying 4-hour and daily structure. The 4-hour formed a candle 2 closure with a V-shaped reversal off a previous high near 1.40620, while the daily candle opened, made a high, and showed a change in state of delivery supporting downside.",
  "key_observation": "Both the daily and 4-hour candles have small wicks supporting downside expansion, with the 4H showing a C2 closure / V-shaped reversal off prior high. Alignment across timeframes signals trend continuation lower on the 15-minute.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Applied the fractal model indicator set to 4-hour and 15-minute to view daily, 4H, and 15M structure simultaneously.",
    "Identified a candle 2 closure on the 4-hour with a V-shaped reversal off the previous high, but noted the large wick means it does not yet support expansion.",
    "Confirmed the daily candle has a small wick — price opened, did not make a relevant low, made a high, and showed a change in state of delivery — supporting downside trend.",
    "Waited for price to sweep a 15-minute high into a fair value gap (point of interest) and form a continuation / protected swing within the higher-timeframe candle.",
    "Anticipated the wick formation and planned entry on retest with stop above the protected swing, targeting a minimum 2R.",
    "Got filled on the retest entry and watched price expand lower with small-wick continuation candles confirming the trend.",
    "Each subsequent candle opened, traded into the protected swing, formed a small wick, and continued expanding lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade was filled on the retest entry and price expanded lower with small-wick continuation candles, hitting the 2R target profitably.",
  "lessons": "For trend/expansion trades, ensure higher-timeframe candles (daily and 4H) all support expansion in the same direction with small wicks. Wait for a protected swing after a sweep into a point of interest before entering, and target a minimum 2R.",
